SIMPLE: undercurrent
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Undercurrent
<hw>Un"der*cur`rent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
current below the surface of water, sometimes flowing in a contrary
direction to that on the surface.</def> <rj><au>Totten.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, figuratively, a tendency of feeling, opinion,
or the like, in a direction contrary to what is publicly shown; an
unseen influence or tendency; <as>as, a strong <ex>undercurrent</ex> of
sentiment in favor of a prisoner</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All the while there was a busy <qex>undercurrent</qex> in her.</q>
<rj><qau>G. Eliot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Undercurrent</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Undercurrent
<hw>Un"der*cur`rent</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Running beneath the
surface; hidden.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Undercurrent</xex>
woe.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Tennyson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Undercut</ent>⟦br⟧
